{meta: title Keeper Of My Heart}
{meta: artist Bob Wills}
{meta: writer Bob Wills and Jerry Irby}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]If again you were just [G7]mine
[C]The sun for me would always shine
[G7]Though fate had ruled that we must part
[C]You're still the keeper of my heart
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]Each night now down upon my knees
[C]I pray that you'll remember me
[G7]When we're many miles apart
[C]You'll be the keeper of my heart
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G7]All alone without your love
[C]I ask our Keeper up above
[G7]To guide your footsteps back to me
[C]Without you life's no good you see
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[G7]The treasured memories that burn
[C]I keep and I will always yearn
[G7]All the love that once was part
[C]Of the keeper of my heart
{end_of_verse}
